1
00:00:03,460 --> 00:00:04,950
Shit. Did the sound of the pages wake you?

2
00:00:05,532 --> 00:00:06,071
Damn.

3
00:00:07,278 --> 00:00:08,422
Anyway, I'm done.

4
00:00:09,206 --> 00:00:11,244
Last night, did we...?

5
00:00:11,284 --> 00:00:14,590
No. You passed out like a sack, completely drunk.

6
00:00:14,948 --> 00:00:16,578
So, I took the chance to read your manuscript.

7
00:00:17,078 --> 00:00:19,124
I have a lot to tell you.

8
00:00:20,898 --> 00:00:24,552
The beginning is very good. Very classic, but very good.

9
00:00:25,071 --> 00:00:28,890
Even though I think it's a shame to describe the hero so much from the start.

10
00:00:29,459 --> 00:00:30,320
But that, that's okay.

11
00:00:30,961 --> 00:00:33,382
On the other hand, the preliminary structure...

12
00:00:33,415 --> 00:00:35,503
What you're saying is interesting,

13
00:00:35,528 --> 00:00:39,074
but I have a headache. I'm not used to drinking that much.

14
00:00:39,266 --> 00:00:43,566
literary criticism.

15
00:00:43,660 --> 00:00:46,794
But this novel, as it is, isn't publishable.

16
00:00:47,350 --> 00:00:47,623
Oh really?

17
00:00:47,850 --> 00:00:50,271
I love your dialogue. You're good at that.

18
00:00:50,948 --> 00:00:54,730
There are huge chunks of it. It's like a play.

19
00:00:55,110 --> 00:00:55,827
There's a lot of talking.

20
00:00:56,577 --> 00:00:57,806
You can feel the influences.

21
00:00:57,932 --> 00:00:59,692
You've read and loved "Nausea".

22
00:01:00,246 --> 00:01:03,038
You've read Camus... You re-read Camus?

23
00:01:03,472 --> 00:01:05,208
What do you do, in life?

24
00:01:05,442 --> 00:01:07,345
PhD in Classics at Paris IV (Sorbonne).

25
00:01:08,754 --> 00:01:11,446
My field of analysis is more poetry.

26
00:01:11,747 --> 00:01:14,414
But I made you some notes.

27
00:01:14,568 --> 00:01:15,961
You annotated my text?

28
00:01:16,308 --> 00:01:17,193
I was afraid I'd forget.

29
00:01:17,367 --> 00:01:19,167
• My whole text? - Well, yes.

30
00:01:19,407 --> 00:01:21,724
Look, page 17. It's too redundant.

31
00:01:21,870 --> 00:01:24,836
And you need to cut all these adverbs.

32
00:01:24,963 --> 00:01:26,344
Okay, I'll do that.

33
00:01:26,491 --> 00:01:28,202
But right now, I have to go.

34
00:01:28,636 --> 00:01:30,474
• But I'm not finished. - No, no.

35
00:01:30,515 --> 00:01:33,654
We could talk about it later. I don't know...

36
00:01:33,848 --> 00:01:34,249
When?

37
00:01:34,696 --> 00:01:36,215
I have a lot to tell you.

38
00:01:36,888 --> 00:01:39,463
I took notes about you, too.

39
00:01:39,896 --> 00:01:41,804
About me? Meaning what?

40
00:01:42,538 --> 00:01:44,115
Your way of sleeping is admirable.

41
00:01:44,455 --> 00:01:47,567
That's nice, but it won't pay the bills.

42
00:01:48,020 --> 00:01:49,234
And you kiss very well.

43
00:01:49,926 --> 00:01:52,519
I have to take a shower, sorry.

44
00:01:53,050 --> 00:01:56,273
Okay. But we have to see each other again.

45
00:01:56,547 --> 00:01:57,128
I wrote everything down here.

46
00:01:57,521 --> 00:01:59,876
This, my parents' place, where I live most of the time.

47
00:02:00,377 --> 00:02:03,643
This, the restaurant where I work Monday to Thursday.

48
00:02:04,196 --> 00:02:06,721
And this, at Julie's, where I sleep on weekends.

49
00:02:07,020 --> 00:02:08,438
There, I think that's everything.

50
00:02:09,645 --> 00:02:10,606
And your number?

51
00:02:12,076 --> 00:02:12,973
Mine?

